bug.short_desc: Moving an resizing a qx.ui.window.Window over complex widget layout selects text content of widgets

long_desc.thetext:
When a window is created which contains lots of widgets with text (eg. qx.ui.form.TextField) in the window and in the document, moving the window or resizing the window selects the text of the window and background.
I've created a testcase (to be run from frontend/application/demobrowser/source/html/test) and a snapshot showing the bug.
To reproduce the bug reload the testcase and then set the cursor to a textfield in the window. Then resize the window to the bottom by dragging the bottom border downwards.
A second buggy effect is dragging the window arround which somehow selects the background widgets text and shows a massive flicker of selections and deselections.

I've created a simple patch to solve the bug.

Created attachment 214 Patch against rev. 8824 of trunk

I've already seen this bad effect and finally I've found a much better alternative. It seems that we really make progress in understanding how to work around browser issues.
The bug is fixed in revison 8831. I've removed the old "unselectable" property and replaced it with a better implementation of the "selectstart" event handler in the EventHandler class.
I hope this has no bad side effects.

Created attachment 216 2nd Patch against rev. 8824 of trunk
This patch should now really fix the bug for resizeMethods "translucient" and "frame"

As a side effect moving of windows is now much faster in IE.

As described already in code: Yes, Opera is - and will always affected - until they offer some variant of support here. Opera has no "selectstart" event, no "unselectable" attribute and no "user-select" CSS3 support. Any idea is welcome, but this is not related to this bug and should maybe described in a new bug as enhancement. Mark as resolved again.
